Audience blind spots:
- Pastel goth is not "soft goth" — the distinction matters to this audience and no competitor explains it clearly
- Readers want permission and validation to wear this aesthetic outside Halloween
- No one addresses the identity dimension — this aesthetic is about balancing softness with edge, and that resonates personally for many readers

**Our Strategic Approach:**

Differentiation: Lead with the emotional and identity logic of pastel goth — you don't choose this aesthetic by accident, and understanding why it works is what separates a truly useful inspo post from a gallery dump. Map the full spectrum from barely-there pastel edge to full kawaii-goth maximalism so readers can find their exact version.

Structure plan: Organise around the spectrum of the aesthetic and then into design categories (colours, motifs, shapes, lengths, moods) so the post functions as both inspo and a genuine guide to finding your version of the look.

Tone direction: Warm, alt-savvy, creatively specific — like a friend who lives in this aesthetic and can explain exactly why certain combos hit.

